text: To hell with that ungrateful jerk Tommy Gunn, *THIS* should have been part of the plot of Rocky V. It was established in the second part that Apollo had a son and daughter. It should have been Rocky mentoring Apollo's son, who after losing his dad has become a lost and angry young man.  Apollo's son has a bad attitude at first, but during his training and his growing bond with Rocky over the loss of someone they both loved, he begins to deal with Apollo's death and his fears about living up to his dad's legacy. Of course, under Rocky's mentorship he quickly shows he too has real talent for the sport and goes pro. Apollo's son would eventually have a real surrogate father/son type bond with Rocky and they would become a solid team in and out of the ring. During this as a side plot they have to deal with Rocky jr feeling left out and beginning to act up to get Rocky's attention.  Apollo's son becomes like family in the end.

text: I heard rumors that Rocky was going to be revealed as suffering some kind of life-threatening illness in this film. I was hoping it was just a rumor but looks like it's true but Creed Jr's firm statement to The Italian Stallion that if he fights he should keep fighting as well gives me hope that Rocky will end up KO'ing whatever illness he has in the film!!! I mean hasn't the man suffered enough with having his hard-earned wealth stolen from him, his first protege's treachery, being estranged from his son not once but twice & losing many of his closest friends & loved ones along the way such as Mickey, Apollo, his beloved wife Adrian & now Paulie too? Keep flying Rock!!!  1 thing about the new trailer that's got me a bit confused is when Creed Jr says he bounced around foster care in & out for yrs but how can that be if his mother, Apollo's widow is still clearly alive & well? Just how could he have been in foster care when he's still got his mom around & not only that, judging by the looks of how she's dressed & her fancy home, The Creed family still maintains the high-end lifestyle that the ol' Master of Disaster earned over his yrs of dominance in the ring!!! Doesn't make sense does it?  Either way, I cannot wait for this spectacular-looking spinoff of 1 of the greatest film franchises of all-time :)

Revelation 20:14-15 And death and hell were cast into the lake of fire. THIS IS THE SECOND DEATH.  And whosoever was not found written in the book of life was cast into the lake of fire.  DOES ANYONE MEASURE UP TO GOD'S STANDARD?  Romans 3:23 For ALL have sinned, and come short of the glory of God.  HOW CAN WE BE SAVED?  John 3:16 For God so loved the world, that he gave his only begotten Son, that whosoever BELIEVETH in him should not perish, but have everlasting life.  Romans 10:9 That if thou shalt confess with thy mouth the Lord Jesus, and shalt BELIEVE in thine heart that God hath raised him from the dead, thou shalt be saved.  Romans 10:10 For with the heart man BELIEVETH unto righteousness; and with the mouth confession is made unto salvation.  WHAT EXACTLY DID HE DO TO SAVE US?  1 Corinthians 15:3-4 For I delivered unto you first of all that which I also received, how that Christ DIED FOR OUR SINS according to the scriptures; And that he WAS BURIED, and that he ROSE AGAIN THE THIRD DAY according to the scriptures:  1 Peter 3:18 For Christ also hath once SUFFERED FOR SINS, the just for the unjust, that he might bring us to God, being put to death in the flesh, but quickened by the Spirit:  HOW ARE WE CLEANED FROM SIN?  Hebrews 9:22 And almost all things are by the law purged WITH BLOOD; and without shedding of blood is no remission.  Colossians 1:20 And, having made peace through THE BLOOD of his cross, by him to reconcile all things unto himself; by him, I say, whether they be things in earth, or things in heaven.  IS IT FREE OR DO WE HAVE TO DO SOMETHING FOR IT?  Ephesians 2:9 For by grace are ye saved through faith; and that NOT OF YOURSELF: it is the GIFT OF GOD:Not of works, lest any man should boast.  Romans 6:23 For the wages of sin is death; but the GIFT OF GOD is eternal life through Jesus Christ our Lord.  CAN YOU BE CERTAIN THAT YOU ARE SAVED?   I John 5:13 These things have I written unto you that believe on the name of the Son of God; THAT YE MAY KNOW that ye have eternal life, and that ye may BELIEVE on the name of the Son of God.  HOW LONG DOES IT LAST?  John 6:47 Verily, verily, I say unto you, He that believeth on me hath EVERLASTING life.  ARE YOU PROTECTED AGAINST LOSING YOUR SALVATION?  Ephesians 4:30 And grieve not the holy Spirit of God, whereby YE ARE SEALED unto the day of redemption.  Jude 1:1 Jude, the servant of Jesus Christ, and brother of James, to them that are sanctified by God the Father, and PRESERVED in Jesus Christ, and called:  CALL ON HIS NAME!  Psalms 116:13  I will take the cup of salvation, and CALL UPON THE NAME OF LORD.   Romans 10:13  For whosoever shall CALL UPON THE NAME OF THE LORD shall be saved.  Pray: LORD I believe I am a sinner. I know I deserve to go to hell. I believe you are the Son of God, and through your shed blood on the cross I have forgiveness of sins, and by your resurrection I am justified.  Please save me!

So much win in this film.
